# Deploy Agent

When the user asks to deploy, ship, push live, or update production, follow this workflow exactly.

## Deploy Target

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| GitHub | `gogg03/Bayou-Blitz` (origin) |
| VPS | `root@76.13.99.190` (Hostinger) |
| App path | `/opt/Bayou-Blitz` |
| Service | `bayou-blitz` (systemd) |
| Frontend | nginx serves `/opt/Bayou-Blitz/dist` |
| Live URL | https://gogg.cloud |

## Workflow

### 1. Pre-flight checks (run in parallel)
```
npx tsc --noEmit                    # zero type errors
npx tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.server.json  # server types clean
git status                          # check working tree
git log --oneline -3                # recent history for commit context
```
If type checks fail, STOP and fix before deploying.

### 2. Git commit & push
- Stage all relevant changes (`git add -A`)
- Do NOT commit `.env`, `node_modules`, `dist/`, `*.db`
- Write a clear commit message summarizing the changes
- Push to origin: `git push origin main` (or current branch)
- Confirm push succeeded before proceeding

### 3. SSH deploy
Run this single SSH command (requires `all` permissions):
```
ssh root@76.13.99.190 "cd /opt/Bayou-Blitz && git pull && npm install && npm run build && systemctl restart bayou-blitz"
```

### 4. Verify
After deploy, verify the service is running:
```
ssh root@76.13.99.190 "systemctl status bayou-blitz --no-pager -l"
```
Report the result to the user. If the service failed, check logs:
```
ssh root@76.13.99.190 "journalctl -u bayou-blitz -n 30 --no-pager"
```

## Rules
- NEVER deploy without passing type checks first
- NEVER force push (`--force`) unless the user explicitly asks
- ALWAYS confirm the branch name before pushing
- If there are uncommitted changes, ask the user for a commit message or draft one
- If the SSH step fails, show the error and suggest fixes — do not retry automatically
